ithout shissar/serubane)</span><hr size=1> Perma rooted aggro is in no way like spell-root aggro. Spell root-aggro is extremely simple, whoever is closest gets hit. Perma rooted mobs do not behave the same way.<br><br>If you've ever backed out of range of a perma-rooted mob while full health, and been summoned back repeatedly while every other melee in the guild was in range, that should tell you that proximity isn't all that important. If you have good aggro, proximity doesn't matter. If you don't, well I guess every little bit helps. <br><br>It's very mob specific of course, AoW (and most stuff in kael) is very much proximity based. On the other hand, Arch Lich, Creator, Cursed, High priest etc. don't seem to care how far away you are as long as you're in melee range. I've tanked them all from further away than people he was ignoring plenty of times, because of knockback/stun, positioning, or whatever else.<br> <p><html><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13986>Kruelty</a><BR><a href=http://www.nightbane.net>Nightbane</a></html></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usinark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/21/02 8:09:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uslashy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slashy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/22/02 4:06:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1691.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   my guess</span><hr size=1> Permarooted NPC = runspeed of 0 is what i think <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=t